  "info": {
    "name": "DynDisc-FactoringDecision-30d-TimeEpoch",
    "_postman_id": "factoring-decision-30d-epoch-v2",
    "description": "FactoringDecision 3-channel cost comparison with time-epoch cashflow tracking.\nMirrors DynDisc2-MultiContract-AR-AP-Cash-timeepoch-mulfun-3 structure.\n\nInvoice: $100K PAM, Mar-01\u2192Mar-31 (30d). 30 daily monitoring PP events.\nCSH CASH-RESERVE-001: $1,000 opening reserve (IED 2026-02-05).\n\nScenario 1 (factoring_inv004): bank=12% APR, reverse=6% APR\n  \u2192 discount APR 24.3% >> reverse 6% \u2192 LOSES every day \u2192 MD=$100,000 at maturity\n\nScenario 2 (factoring_inv005): bank=30% APR, reverse=25% APR\n  \u2192 discount APR 24.3% < both \u2192 WINS Day 1 \u2192 PP=$98,066.67 on Mar-02\n\nEPOCH TABLE (buyer cash perspective):\n  Ep0  2026-02-05  CSH           +$1,000.00   balance=$1,000.00\n  Ep1  2026-03-02  INV-005 DISC  -$98,066.67  balance=-$97,066.67\n  Ep2  2026-03-31  INV-004 NONE  -$100,000.00 balance=-$197,066.67\n  Discount saving: $1,933.33 (vs face $200,000)\n\nAll payoffs verified against ACTUS engine console output.",
